och\""}, {"ref": "went through Syria and Cilicia", "text": "<b>went through Syria and Cilicia</b>  These are provinces in Asia Minor, north of the island of Cyprus."}, {"ref": "strengthening the churches", "text": "\"making the churches spiritually strong\""}]}, {"id": "16-01", "tn": [{"ref": "behold", "text": "The word \u201cbehold\u201d alerts us to a new person in the story. Your language may have a way of doing this. English uses \u201cThere was a man who was\u2026\u201d"}, {"ref": "the son of a Jewish woman who believed", "text": "\"the son of a Jewish woman who believed in Christ\""}, {"ref": "He was well spoken of", "text": "\"Timothy had a good reputation\" or \"the believers said good things about him\""}, {"ref": "Paul wanted him to travel with him; so he took him", "text": "\"Paul wanted Timothy to travel with him (Paul); so Paul took Timothy.\" All other third person pronouns (he, him, his) throughout these verses refer to Timothy."}, {"ref": "his father was a Greek ", "text": "As a Greek, Timothy's father would not have personally circumcised Timothy; so Paul circumcised him. Circumcision was often performed by a Jewish Rabbi, such as Paul."}]}, {"id": "16-04", "tn": [{"ref": "they went", "text": "This pronoun refers to Paul, Silas, and Timothy."}, {"ref": "for them to obey", "text": "\"for the church members to obey\" or \"for the believers to obey.\""}, {"ref": "that had been written by the apostles and elders in Jerusalem", "text": "\"that the apostles and elders in Jerusalem had written.\" (See: [[en:ta:translate:Active]])"}, {"ref": "the churches were strengthened", "text": "\"Paul, Silas, and Timothy strengthened the churches.\" (See: [[en:ta:translate:Active]])"}]}, {"id": "16-06", "tn": [{"ref": "Phrygia and Galatia", "text": "These are provinces in Asia. (See: [[:en:ta:translate:translatenames]])"}, {"ref": "Mysia... Bithynia", "text": "These are two more provinces in Asia."}, {"ref": "they had been forbidden by the Holy Spirit", "text": "\"the